{
  "stem": "4830.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My name is Norbert Kerenyi.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was born Norbert Kohn in Hungary in January 15, 1928.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Budapest.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My family-- my father and my mother both-- were born outside of Budapest.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And when I was born, our family already had two children.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had an older brother and an older sister.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] After me, in 1929, we had one more member of the family who is my younger brother.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So for all intents and purposes, I was a middle child.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My older brother's name was Gabor, and he was born in 1924, April.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my sister was-- her name is Idit, and she was born in 1925, August.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my younger brother, Ervin, was born in 1929, September, and I think I told you his name is Ervin.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would rather tell you which was not.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Gabor, did not survive.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The rest of the immediate family survived.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On the other hand-- and this is why I mentioned that our family came originally from the country-- from the wider family, very few people survived.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "As you know, those who lived in Budapest survived in a larger percentage.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And those in the country died.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If I count just aunts, uncles, and cousins, I lost 39 members of my family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, most of them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think that the younger ones were killed in Auschwitz immediately, as they got there, and the others died in different concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One of them I particularly know-- my uncle who participated in the Auschwitz revolt that destroyed [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] one of the chambers.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was killed there by the Germans.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Miklos, or in English, Nicholas.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he was on my mother's side.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "His family name was Droth, D-R-O-T-H.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother's maiden name.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
